  "text": "Learning that is done in the studio by paying attention to some of these aspects can indirectly carry the character values that exist in the dancer himself, Riyaningsih said that \"learning traditional dance can have a positive influence in building the character of students who: 1) religiosity; 2) honesty; 3) responsibility and cooperation; 4) tolerance; 5) discipline. Therefore, it is considered very important to be able to pay attention to several aspects that support dance learning that produce good potential dancers\" [CITATION_1] .",
